thread.title: George Darnton
thread.title_full: Ink Station reviewed by George Darnton

author: George Darnton
title: George Darnton
text:
Purchased the Ink Station generic replacement cartridges for my Canon printer at 1/3 the cost of genuine elsewhere, installed with no problems and functioning correctly, can't ask for more than that.
Damn it, Canon want more than I paid for the printer just for a pair of cartridges!
My only criticism is the courier company driver who was unable to read my specific delivery instructions that were printed on the parcel and highlighted in yellow and left the parcel in full view at the front door. Minor issue I guess but I wonder what would have happened had the parcel been stolen.
